The paper deals with the problem of hypothesis selection under local differential privacy, which involves designing algorithms that output a distribution from a set of probability distributions that is close to an unknown distribution while satisfying local differential privacy constraints. This problem is related to several areas of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), cryptography (cs.CR), data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), and computational complexity (cs.CC). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
